ZH: 我今天在超市里巧遇了老同学。
EN: I coincidentally ran into an old classmate at the supermarket today.

ZH: 昨天晚上我在餐厅里巧遇了我的偶像。
EN: Last night I happened to meet my idol at the restaurant.

ZH: 他们两个人在街上巧遇，感觉非常巧合。
EN: They coincidentally bumped into each other on the street, feeling very coincidental.

ZH: 她在火车站巧遇了一个让她心动的男生。
EN: She coincidentally met a boy who made her heart beat at the train station.

ZH: 我们巧遇了一场暴风雪，被困在了山里。
EN: We encountered a blizzard by chance and got trapped in the mountains.

ZH: 他们在图书馆里巧遇，不约而同地开始了研究合作。
EN: They coincidentally met in the library and started a research collaboration.

ZH: 她在大学里巧遇了一个帮她度过难关的朋友。
EN: She met a friend who helped her get through tough times in college.

ZH: 我们巧遇了一个天使般的老太太，在危险时为我们提供了帮助。
EN: We encountered an angelic old lady who helped us in a dangerous situation.

ZH: 骑自行车的路上我巧遇了我的弟弟。
EN: I coincidentally met my brother while riding a bike on the road.

ZH: 她在健身房巧遇了一个有趣的陌生人。
EN: She met an interesting stranger at the gym by chance.

ZH: 我们在游乐园里巧遇了一个长得像卡通人物的小孩。
EN: We encountered a child who looked like a cartoon character at the amusement park.

ZH: 昨天夜晚在酒吧里，我巧遇了以前的同事。
EN: Last night at the bar, I happened to meet my former colleague.

ZH: 她在音乐会上巧遇了自己的偶像。
EN: She coincidentally met her idol at the concert.

ZH: 他巧遇了一个擅长烹饪的厨师，为他打造了一场美味的晚餐。
EN: He encountered a chef who was good at cooking and prepared a delicious dinner for him.

ZH: 经过数年的离别，他们巧遇在了一个偏远的小镇上。
EN: After years of separation, they coincidentally met in a remote town.

ZH: 我们在酒吧里巧遇了一个穿着怪异的小丑表演者。
EN: We encountered a clown performer with a weird outfit at the bar.

ZH: 她不经意间巧遇了一个有趣的陌生人，成为了好朋友。
EN: She accidentally met an interesting stranger and became good friends.

ZH: 我们巧遇了一个重要的商务合作机会，让我们感到非常幸运。
EN: We came across an important business collaboration opportunity, which made us feel very fortunate.

ZH: 在火车站里，我意外地巧遇了一个曾经在我公司工作过的同事。
EN: At the train station, I coincidentally met a former colleague who once worked in my company.

ZH: 偶然巧遇的机会让我们重新联络上了多年不见的老朋友。
EN: The chance encounter brought us back in touch with old friends we hadn't seen in years.
